spine
deformities
and
cystic
fibrosis
patients
with
cystic
fibrosis
have
an
increased
risk
for
developing
kyphosis
and
scoliosis
the
risk
for
both
kyphosis
and
scoliosis
increases
with
age
the
severity
of
kyphosis
did
not
appear
greater
in
the
older
age
groups
patients
with
retarded
bone
age
may
be
more
likely
to
have
a
significant
spinal
deformity
the
presence
of
spine
deformity
does
not
correlate
with
the
severity
of
pulmonary
involvement
height
weight
serum
protein
and
albumin
in
patients
with
cystic
fibrosis
